{
  "texts": [
    "Each trial timed out at 10 s, after which the trial was considered failed.",
    "We tested a range of output gains for the comparison of online linear decoders and RNNs used for Fig. 5c (includes data from trial days 1853 and 1855) to ensure that performance differences were not due to variation in decoded output magnitudes.",
    "The range of gain values was determined on each session day by a closed-loop block (preceding data collection) where the experimenter hand-tuned values until the participant's control degraded.",
    "Hand-tuning of gain values was done for the linear decoder and RNN, separately.",
    "Each session day had 4-5 equally spaced gain values for each decoder."
  ]
}